&lt;MAI Plc>, the financial services andadvertising group, has asked S.G. Warburg and Co Ltd to arrangea 100 mln dlr multiple option facility which will restructure apart of the company's exisiting banking arrangements, bankingsources said.    The financing will be for five years and involves acommitted backstop facility and an uncommitted tender panel forcash advances in dollars or other available currencies.    The committed part of the transaction will carry a facilityfee of 7.5 basis points and drawings will be at a margin of 15basis points.    There also will be a utilization fee of five basis pointsif the underwriting banks are called upon to provide more than30 pct of the facility. Reuter&#3;